because the spring-boot-starter-data-redis contains both `jedis` and `lettuce`, if you exclude `lettuce`, the default connection should use `jedis`.

For those using Maven instead of Gradle, and following Dolphin&#39;s [answer][1], you ought to exclude `lettuce-core` artifact in your `pom.xml` file:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-data-redis&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;exclusions&gt;
            &lt;exclusion&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;io.lettuce&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;lettuce-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;/exclusion&gt;
        &lt;/exclusions&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

And add `jedis` Maven dependency:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;redis.clients&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;jedis&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

---

Note: If you&#39;re using Spring Boot 2.5.x, then the version of `spring-boot-starter-data-redis` will require `jedis` version `3.9.0`. This is due to the breaking changes introduced when moving from Jedis 3 to Jedis 4 (see [this][2] answer).


  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/67489646/1346996
  [2]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/72188180/1346996

